title: Jose the Stockholder
description: The hotel manager is being critical of Jose. While at a stockholders meeting of the chain that owns the Park Central, the managers job is in jeopardy. Jose, owns one share of stock and saves his bosses job.

title: Jose and the Brat
description: Jose gets assigned the task of baby-sitting a 10-year-old brat who takes pleasure in kicking him in the shins.

title: Speak for Yourself, Jose
description: Jose's nephew asks Jose to speak on his behalf at a dinner party. Jose, embarrassed by his lack of eloquence asks Mr. Phillips to speak instead.

title: Jose's Hot Dog Caper
description: Jose and Glick accidentally encounter diamond thieves.

title: Blood from Two Turnips
description: Mr. Phillips requires all employees donate blood to the Red Cross. Only two squeamish babies try to get out of it-- Glick and Jiminez.

title: Danny Thomas, I Love You
description: Danny Thomas checks into the Park Central but due to a mix-up, the penthouse is not available. Jose comes to the rescue and gives Danny his quarters.

title: Jose on the Ledge or the Crystal Room
Jose, the Flower Thief
description: Jose and house detective Byron Glick catch a little old lady picking flowers in the park. However, a cop catches Jose with the evidence and arrests him. At his trial, Glick acts as his defense attorney.
